headline: Goldman Sachs downgrades General Mills, Conagra on cost pressures, weak demand
summary: Investing.com -- Goldman Sachs downgraded shares of General Mills (NYSE:GIS) and Conagra Brands (NYSE:CAG), citing ongoing cost pressures and sluggish demand for packaged food products, while maintaining its Sell rating on Kraft Heinz (NASDAQ:KHC).

headline: Consumer Goods Giants Slim Down to Spur Growth
summary: Scale for scale's sake appears to have become passé, with conglomerates jockeying for market share with a more focused brand identity.

headline: 3 S&P 500 Stocks Walking a Fine Line
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is home to the biggest and most well-known companies in the market, making it a go-to index for investors seeking stability. But not all large-cap stocks are created equal - some are struggling with slowing growth, declining margins, or increased competition.
